🌈DENSITY LAYERING IS ALWAYS A HIT🌈
.
.
Students always come in with a little bit of knowledge on density from 5th grade but we are building on that knowledge! And what better way to do that then with a fun, rainbow demonstration?!🩵 
.
We pour 5 liquids into a graduated cylinder one at a time (syrup, dawn soap, water, vegetable oil, & rubbing alcohol) and see how they layer! Fun fact: it ends up being rainbow order 😉 Then we add a few objects to compare densities of solids to that of our liquids! So many good conversations and density comparisons!👏🏼
.
I don’t have the paper on tpt for those asking because it was created by an old team member!

Let’s talk Student Social- Emotional learning! 💛
.

I think I found my new favorite resource to share with my students!! I am a huge believer in Maslow before Bloom and these “Little Talk” cards are the perfect way to start off a Monday or to bring out with a few extra minutes of class!! Each card addresses a different theme or topic and comes with ready made prompts to get students talking about their emotions!
